  Key design decisions

  Strands vs ADK differences (clearly commented in code):
  - ADK: LlmAgent + InMemoryRunner.run_async() → async Event stream parsed with _format_event()
  - Strands: Agent(model, tools, callback_handler) + synchronous agent(prompt) — no asyncio wiring needed
  - Tools are closures wrapped with strands_tool() instead of plain functions — captures inbox, outbox, and log_callback
  - Each tool embeds its own [tool_use] / [result] logging via log_callback (no framework event parsing)

  New feature — inbox file editor:
  - PUT /api/file/inbox/<path> endpoint in web_app.py
  - ✏ Edit button appears in the viewer toolbar for inbox files only
  - Yellow edit bar with 💾 Save and ✕ Cancel — discards edits with confirmation if switching files

  Workshop materials (6 exercises updated for Strands)

  All 6 exercises were rewritten to reflect Strands SDK concepts, the @tool decorator pattern, the closure-based tool
  factory, the callback_handler, and the new in-browser editor feature. Workshop placeholders and # WORKSHOP comments
  are present throughout both Python files.

